heaviest_rainfall.status: Today's storm ranked 7th for total rainfall with 23.86mm having fallen, indicating an exceptionally wet day.  8.3mm per hour fell at points during the storm which lasted 31.0 hours.  Record-breaking rain fell on 09 November 2025 with a total accumulation of 47.89mm over 144.8 hours and falling at a rate of 24.6mm per hour at times.

heaviest_rainrate.status: Today, the rain fell at an intense rate peaking at 27.6mm per hour, one of the heaviest downpours recorded and ranked 2nd from our records.  The precipitation lasted 2.6 hours and dumped 6.1mm in total.  The rain rate reached 34.3mm per hour on 02 September 2025, and resulted in 21.19mm of rain over 15.0 hours.  This is the highest rate recorded by our weather station.

longest_rain.status: Ranked 7th for lengthiest precipitation event, today's storm spanned 31.0 hours and was characterized by a peak rain intensity of 8.3mm per hour.  23.86mm of rain fell in total.  The longest rain storm on record lasted 144.8 hours on 09 November 2025 when 47.89mm of rain fell and at one point was falling at 24.6mm per hour.
